    <note>Qian(1) Yi [146] His great grandfather was Wusu Wang, Qian(1) Liu [3036], first king of Wuyue. His grandfather Yuanguan [3042], Liu's successor, was Shen(2) Chengli's [1442] father-in-law. Yuanguan's eldest son, Zong [3039], succeeded him and was Yi's father. Zong was forced to abdicate in favor of his brother Shu [3037], Weiyan's [8006] father, who voluntarily returned the territory under his control to Song. Yuanguan's father-in-law was Fufeng jun Ma(2) Zhuo [3662]. Yi was Yanyuan's [7010] father and Xie's [145] grandfather. His brother, Kun [3035], moved to Suzhou. Ruoshui [8005] was a clansman. Yi was Zhang(1) Zonggu's [7170] father-in-law, and the maternal grandfather of Zhang(1) Shengqing [275]. XCB, 90.9b; SS, 307.9a-10b; Xianchun Linan zhi, 65.5b; Liangzhe jin, 4.10b; Su Song, WJ, 62.9a. CBD, 5, 4060.</note>
